data.title: Morgan Wallen Reveals Knoxville Show With HARDY, ERNEST: 'I’m Coming Home'
data.meta_description: The East Tennessee-born singer-songwriter announced plans to add a tour stop at Neyland Stadium this fall in Knoxville, Tennessee.
data.text:
Morgan Wallen announced plans to take the stage this fall at Neyland Stadium in Knoxville, Tennessee.

“I’m coming home,” Wallen wrote in his caption on Instagram on Monday morning (July 15) as he announced the show, set for September 22. Tickets will be available on Wednesday (July 17) at 11 a.m. ET, the “Lies Lies Lies” singer confirmed. The lineup for the Sneedville, Tennessee-born artist's Knoxville concert will include HARDY and ERNEST.

“I've had the honor of playing in a lot of college, MLB and NFL stadiums the past two years, but getting to play to my hometown at Neyland Stadium, nothing tops this for a boy from East Tennessee,” Wallen said in a press release on Monday morning.
